{
  "id": "jsonbored_awesome-claude_1126",
  "repo_name": "jsonbored/awesome-claude",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/jsonbored/awesome-claude",
  "base_commit": "f90f07e9a1f749725da1f0c96b34e3ea3eda2641",
  "pr_number": 1126,
  "issue_number": 1125,
  "issue_title": "Discord notification `truncate` overshoots its length cap by 2 and splits surrogate pairs (garbled emoji in maintainer alerts)",
  "issue_body": "**Labels:** bug, submissions\n**Component:** `@heyclaude` submission gate (Cloudflare Worker) \u2014 Discord notifications\n**Affected file:** `apps/submission-gate/src/notifications.ts` (`truncate`, lines 52\u201358)\n\n## Summary\n\nThe submission gate's Discord notification helper truncates field/description/title text with:\n\n```ts\nfunction truncate(value: unknown, limit: number) {\n  const text = String(value || \"\")\n    .replace(/\\s+/g, \" \")\n    .trim();\n  if (text.length <= limit) return text;\n  return `${text.slice(0, Math.max(0, limit - 1)).trimEnd()}...`;\n}\n```\n\nThis has two correctness defects:\n\n1. **It overshoots the requested limit by 2.** It reserves only `limit - 1` characters for the content but then appends a **3-character** `\"...\"`, so the result is up to `limit + 2` characters \u2014 it never honors `limit`.\n2. **It splits surrogate pairs.** `String.prototype.slice` cuts by UTF-16 code units, so when a non-BMP character (emoji, many CJK extension/symbol characters) straddles the cut point, the result ends in a **lone high surrogate**. Rendered, that becomes a replacement character (`\ufffd`) in the maintainer's Discord notification.\n\nBoth behaviors are inconsistent with the codebase's other two truncation helpers, which get this right:\n\n- `truncateForQueue` (`apps/submission-gate/src/index.ts:345`) uses `slice(0, maxLength - 3)` + `\"...\"` \u2014 reserves the full ellipsis width.\n- `oneLine` (`apps/submission-gate/src/drafts.ts:149`) uses `Array.from(normalized)` and `codePoints.slice(0, 157)` + `\"...\"` for a cap of 160 \u2014 code-point-aware **and** reserves 3.\n\n`truncate` should match that contract: result length `\u2264 limit`, and never emit a partial code point.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nFor any input and `limit`, `truncate(text, limit)`:\n- returns at most `limit` characters, and\n- never ends in a lone/partial surrogate (no `\ufffd` from a split emoji).\n\n## Actual behavior (reproduced)\n\n```\ntruncate(\"x\".repeat(300), 220)  -> length 222   (declared cap 220)\ntruncate(\"x\".repeat(300), 256)  -> length 258   (title cap == Discord's hard 256-char title limit)\n\ntruncate(\"a\".repeat(218) + \"\ud83d\ude00\" + \"tail\", 220)\n  -> \"\u2026aa\\uD83D...\"   // ends in a lone high surrogate (\ud83d\ude00 split mid-pair) \u2192 renders as \ufffd\n```\n\n## Impact\n\n- **Garbled emoji in maintainer Discord alerts (user-visible).** Field values (`DISCORD_MAX_FIELD_LENGTH = 220`), the description (`DISCORD_MAX_DESCRIPTION_LENGTH = 260`), and the PR subject (`compactPrSubject(..., 120)`) are all run through `truncate`, and all are built from contributor-controlled text (PR title, validation/CI summary, rationale) that routinely contains emoji. An emoji near the cut point produces a `\ufffd` in the embed the maintainer sees. This is the practically reachable defect.\n- **Cap is not honored.** Every truncated value is 2 characters longer than the limit the caller asked for. For the embed title the configured cap (`DISCORD_MAX_TITLE_LENGTH = 256`) equals Discord's hard title limit, so the off-by-2 leaves no safety margin there; the helper's contract (\"stay within `limit`\") is simply not met for any caller.\n\nSeverity is notification quality/correctness, not a gate-decision or security issue \u2014 but it degrades the maintainer-facing alerts and contradicts the repo's own truncation convention.\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Trigger any gate decision whose notification field text exceeds its cap (e.g. a long CI/validation summary, or a PR title containing an emoji near the 120-char subject boundary).\n2. Inspect the Discord embed (or call `buildDiscordDecisionPayload` directly and measure field/title lengths).\n\n**Result:** the truncated value is `limit + 2` characters and, if a non-BMP character sat at the boundary, ends in a replacement character. **Expected:** `\u2264 limit` characters and no partial code point.\n\n## Root cause\n\n`limit - 1` reserves one character for an ellipsis that is actually three characters (`\"...\"`), and `slice` operates on UTF-16 code units rather than Unicode code points. The sibling helpers `truncateForQueue` and `oneLine` already encode the correct pattern.\n\n## Proposed fix\n\nMake `truncate` code-point-aware and reserve the full ellipsis width, mirroring `oneLine`:\n\n```ts\nfunction truncate(value: unknown, limit: number) {\n  const text = String(value || \"\")\n    .replace(/\\s+/g, \" \")\n    .trim();\n  const codePoints = Array.from(text);\n  if (codePoints.length <= limit) return text;\n  const keep = Math.max(0, limit - 3);\n  return `${codePoints.slice(0, keep).join(\"\").trimEnd()}...`;\n}\n```\n\nThis guarantees `result.length <= limit`, never splits a surrogate pair, and stays consistent with `truncateForQueue`/`oneLine`. (If a single-character ellipsis `\"\u2026\"` is preferred to preserve more content, reserve 1 instead of 3 \u2014 but the slice must still be code-point-based.)\n\n## Acceptance criteria / test plan\n\n`truncate` is exercised indirectly via `buildDiscordDecisionPayload` in `tests/submission-gate-worker.test.ts` (~lines 505\u2013561), but every fixture uses short text that never reaches the truncation branch, so no test pins the buggy output. Add coverage:\n\n- [ ] `truncate(longText, 220).length <= 220` (and similarly for 256, 260).\n- [ ] `truncate(\"a\".repeat(218) + \"\ud83d\ude00\" + \"tail\", 220)` contains no replacement character and no lone surrogate (e.g. `Array.from(result)` has no `\ufffd`, and the string round-trips through `encodeURIComponent` without throwing on a lone surrogate).\n- [ ] Inputs at or below `limit` are returned unchanged (existing `buildDiscordDecisionPayload` fixtures stay green \u2014 they use short text and are unaffected).\n\n## Notes for reviewers\n\n- Verified against `main`: `notifications.ts:57` uses `slice(0, Math.max(0, limit - 1))` + `\"...\"`; reproduced both the `+2` overshoot and the surrogate split shown above.\n- Distinct from the two correct truncators already in the repo (`truncateForQueue`, `oneLine`) \u2014 this is a consistency fix that brings the third in line.\n- Searched open and closed issues/PRs on `JSONbored/awesome-claude` for truncate / Discord / emoji / ellipsis / notification \u2014 no existing report. Unrelated to the base64/`atob` UTF-8 decode issue (#1114) and the `tierFromFlags` risk-tier issue; this is purely the notification truncation helper.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-05T21:36:44.000Z",
